Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: django-site-local-middleware
Version: 2020.12.3
Summary: adds .local:port to the site domain links for local development if settings.DEBUG is True
Home-page: https://github.com/andrewp-as-is/django-site-local-middleware.py
License: Unlicense
Description: <!--
        https://readme42.com
        -->
        
        
        [![](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/django-site-local-middleware.svg?maxAge=3600)](https://pypi.org/project/django-site-local-middleware/)
        [![](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Unlicense-blue.svg?longCache=True)](https://unlicense.org/)
        
        ### Installation
        ```bash
        $ [sudo] pip install django-site-local-middleware
        ```
        
        #### Examples
        `settings.py`
        
        ```python
        DEBUG=True
        
        MIDDLEWARE = [
            ...
            'django_site_local_middleware.middleware.SiteLocalMiddleware'
            ...
        ]
        ```
        
        `/etc/hosts`
        ```
        127.0.0.1   site.com.local
        ```
        
        
        ```bash
        $ python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000
        ```
        
        before|after
        -|-
        `<a href="http://site.com/">`|`<a href="http://site.com.local:8000/">`
        
